						<summary>

						

						<p>On the east face of the <hi rend="italic">Garuḍa-staṁbha</hi> in front of the Chennakēśava temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1566, Tāraṇa, Śrāvaṇa śu. 15 = 1644 A.D., August 8 (Thursday), f.d.t. ·06</hi></p>						

						<p>It states that Pālum Vōbannaṁgāru, son of Tirupatayaṁgār, grandson of Sarparāju, belonging to Maudgalya-gōtra, Āpastaṁbha-sūtra and Yajuśśākhā, set up this <hi rend="italic">garuḍa-staṁbha,</hi> after laving the feet of god (?) Chaṁnnarāya of Mācharla.</p>						

						</summary>
